---

<div id='sidebar' class='relative flex basis-1/3 flex-col gap-2 text-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-950'>
	<div class='flex h-15 flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 border-b-1 border-white/10 p-3'>
		<a href='https://github.com/Pine1611' target='_blank' class='rounded-[3px] ring-1 ring-slate-50/20'>
			<img
				alt='Github@IamPine'
				src='https://img.shields.io/badge/%40IamPine-%20?logo=github&logoSize=24&label=Github&labelColor=%23343434&color=%23181717'
			/>
		</a>
		<a
			href='https://github.com/Pine1611/astro-holidays-calendar'
			target='_blank'
			class='rounded-[3px] ring-1 ring-slate-50/20'
		>
			<img
				alt='Static Badge'
				src='https://img.shields.io/badge/src-%20?logo=git&logoColor=%23F05032&logoSize=24&labelColor=%23343434&color=%23F05032'
			/>
		</a>
	</div>

	<div
		id='widgets'
		class='mb-5 flex flex-col gap-5 p-3 *:rounded-xl *:bg-slate-950 *:p-1 *:dark:inset-ring *:dark:inset-ring-white/10'
	>
		<div>
			<h3 class='px-3 pt-0.5 pb-1.5 text-sm/5 text-gray-400 uppercase dark:text-white/50'>Holidays Calendar</h3>
			<div
				class='rounded-lg bg-white/10 p-5 inset-ring inset-ring-white/10 dark:bg-white/5 dark:inset-ring-white/5'
			>
				<p>This is simple National Holidays Calendar I have done with Astro and Fullcalendar.io</p>
				<p>
					The holiday data is taken from the API I built at <a
						class='text-slate-600 transition hover:text-slate-400'
						href='https://pine1611.github.io/holidays/'>this repository.</a
					>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class='bg-slate-950'>
			<h3 class='px-3 pt-0.5 pb-1.5 text-sm/5 text-gray-400 uppercase dark:text-white/50'>Tech Stacks</h3>
			<ul
				class='flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-white/5 p-5 inset-ring inset-ring-white/10 dark:inset-ring-white/5'
			>
				<li>
					<a href='/'>
						<img
							alt='NodeJS'
							src='https://img.shields.io/badge/NodeJS-%20?logo=nodedotjs&logoColor=%235FA04E&labelColor=%23343434&color=%235FA04E'
						/>
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href='/'>
						<img
							alt='Javascript'
							src='https://img.shields.io/badge/Javascript-%20?logo=javascript&logoColor=%23F7DF1E&labelColor=%23343434&color=%23F7DF1E'
						/>
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href='https://astro.build/' target='_blank'>
						<img
							alt='Astro'
							src='https://img.shields.io/badge/Astro-%20?logo=astro&logoColor=%23BC52EE&labelColor=2A2A2A&color=%23BC52EE'
						/>
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href='https://react.dev' target='_blank'>
						<img
							alt='React Dev'
							src='https://img.shields.io/badge/React-%20?logo=react&logoColor=%2361DAFB&labelColor=%23343434&color=%2361DAFB'
						/>
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href='https://tailwindcss.com/' target='_blank'>
						<img
							alt='Tailwindcss'
							src='https://img.shields.io/badge/TailwindCSS-%20?logo=tailwindcss&logoColor=%2306B6D4&labelColor=%23343434&color=%2306B6D4'
						/>
					</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<a
						class='flex flex-row items-center justify-center'
						href='https://fullcalendar.io/'
						target='_blank'
					>
						<span class='block rounded-l-[3px] bg-[#343434] p-1'>
							<img
								alt='Fullcalendar'
								class='h-3 w-3'
								src='data:image/png;base64,'
							/>
						</span>
						<span class='rounded-r-[3px] bg-sky-800 px-1 py-0.5 text-xs text-white'>Fullcalendar.io</span>
					</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div>
			<h3 class='px-3 pt-0.5 pb-1.5 text-sm/5 text-gray-400 uppercase dark:text-white/50'>
				Knowledge and outstanding issues
			</h3>
			<div
				class='rounded-lg bg-white/10 p-5 inset-ring inset-ring-white/10 dark:bg-white/5 dark:inset-ring-white/5'
			>
				<div>
					<span class='mb-3 font-mono text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400'>knowledge</span>
					<p>
						The purpose of this project is to help me practice building projects using Astro, React and
						TailwindCSS.
					</p>
				</div>
				<span class='mb-3 font-mono text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400'>issues</span>
				<p>
					This current version is very very simple, I don't have custom style for Fullcalendar yet, but I will
					try to do it as soon as possible.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<a
		href='https://ipine.net'
		target='_blank'
		class='absolute bottom-2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 text-sm text-gray-200'>ipine.net</a
	>
</div>
